"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-paris-olympics-2024-meet-south-africas-gymnastics-team-caitlin-rooskrantz-breaking\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 63, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15, \"end\": 18, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9840256226223087, \"rank\": 0.016233090047897015, \"text\": \"Sky\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024: Meet South Africa's GYMNASTICS team  South Africa will be represented by one competitor in gymnastics competition at the Paris Olympics 2024.\", \"from\": 65, \"to\": 366, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 107, \"end\": 110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9840256226223087, \"rank\": 0.016233090047897015, \"text\": \"Sky\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 262, \"end\": 274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2478226451190822e-17, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Get to know her better \\u2026  South Africa will be represented byonecompetitor ingymnasticscompetition at theParis Olympics 2024.\", \"from\": 367, \"to\": 492, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 393, \"end\": 405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2478226451190822e-17, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bet Anytime, Anywhere Quick and Easy with Betway  Caitlin Rooskrantzwill battle for the medals in the women's artistic events.\", \"from\": 494, \"to\": 620, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 536, \"end\": 542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Betway\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Betway\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Betway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Betway\"}, {\"begin\": 544, \"end\": 551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caitlin_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.3936880065823073e-13, \"text\": \"Caitlin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caitlin_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caitlin_Thomas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rooskrantz, 22,\\u00a0qualified for the games by virtue of her individual results, through the all-around event at the2023 World Artistic Gymnastics Championshipsin Antwerp in Belgium.\", \"from\": 622, \"to\": 800, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 754, \"end\": 764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artistic_gymnastics\", \"score\": 0.9999996812589924, \"rank\": 3.187410499484814e-07, \"text\": \"Gymnastics\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artistic_gymnastics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artistic_gymnastics\"}, {\"begin\": 781, \"end\": 788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antwerp\", \"score\": 0.9999999828432921, \"rank\": 1.6387702782941784e-08, \"text\": \"Antwerp\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antwerp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antwerp\"}, {\"begin\": 792, \"end\": 799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999999639039749, \"rank\": 1.8200258689571753e-08, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She attended Parktown High School for Girls.\", \"from\": 802, \"to\": 846, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She had planned to have a gap year\\u00a0to focus on competing at the Olympics, though those plans were changed due to the\\u00a0Covid-19 pandemic.\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 983, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2022, she enrolled in the University of Johannesburg\\u00a0and began studying marketing management.\", \"from\": 985, \"to\": 1081, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She comes from an athletic family: her father played football, and her older brother was involved in field hockey and cricket.\", \"from\": 1083, \"to\": 1209, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her father died when she was eight.\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1246, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her mother gave up working full-time as a nurse to support Rooskrantz's gymnastics career.\", \"from\": 1247, \"to\": 1337, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She finished 61st in the qualifying stage\\u00a0of the delayed Tokyo Olympics 2020 and did not qualify for any finals.\", \"from\": 1339, \"to\": 1451, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her score was a personal best.\", \"from\": 1452, \"to\": 1482, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For the latest Paris Olympics 2024 news, bookmarkThe South African website'sdedicated section  Founded in 1881, the International Gymnastics Federation is theoldest international sports federation in the world.\", \"from\": 1484, \"to\": 1694, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1600, \"end\": 1635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Gymnastics Federation\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The origin of gymnastics dates to antiquity, when it was recommended by philosophers as a way of combining physical exercise with intellectual activity.\", \"from\": 1696, \"to\": 1848, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The sport grew in popularity during the 19th century as an increasing number of competitions were formed, including the gymnastics competition at the newly revived Olympic Games in Athens in 1896.\", \"from\": 1850, \"to\": 2046, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2031, \"end\": 2037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999867418411, \"rank\": 1.3258182800388157e-08, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Artistic gymnastics is composed of a number of individual competitions on different apparatus, as well as a team competition involving gender-specific apparatus.\", \"from\": 2048, \"to\": 2209, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Each piece of apparatus requires different skills.\", \"from\": 2211, \"to\": 2261, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Men compete across the floor exercise, pommel horse, rings, vault, parallel bars, and horizontal bar, while women's events include the vault, uneven bars, balance beam, and floor exercise.\", \"from\": 2263, \"to\": 2451, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Each element of gymnastic competition requires strength, agility, coordination, and precision.\", \"from\": 2453, \"to\": 2547, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Up until 2004, gymnastic routines at the Games were evaluated with a maximum of 10 points, but from 2005 the mode of scoring changed to a combination of a D score (difficulty/content of the exercise) and an E score (execution) to allow for a greater variation between athletes' performances.\", \"from\": 2549, \"to\": 2840, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Changes to the scoring system were first considered following the Montreal 1976 Olympic Games, when Romanian gymnast Nadia Comaneci became the first competitor in history to earn a perfect score of 10 for her routine on the uneven bars during the team competition.\", \"from\": 2842, \"to\": 3106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2942, \"end\": 2950, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"score\": 0.704659392208526, \"rank\": 0.41854665693358556, \"text\": \"Romanian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\"}, {\"begin\": 2959, \"end\": 2973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadia_Com\\u0103neci\", \"score\": 0.9999999839878911, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nadia Comaneci\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadia_Com\\u0103neci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadia_Com\\u0103neci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Artistic gymnastics was introduced at the very first Olympic Games of the modern era in 1896 and has been included in every edition since.\", \"from\": 3108, \"to\": 3246, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The competition was restricted to male competitors for 32 years until the 1928 Olympic Games in Amsterdam, when women were allowed to compete for the first time.\", \"from\": 3248, \"to\": 3409, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3344, \"end\": 3353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.407191216647768e-14, \"text\": \"Amsterdam\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It wasn't until 1952 that the women's programme was developed with seven events, and then later stabilised at six events, as has been the case since the 1960 Games in Rome.\", \"from\": 3411, \"to\": 3583, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3578, \"end\": 3582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"score\": 0.9907196015026551, \"rank\": 0.009004706147206777, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are eight events on the men's programme.\", \"from\": 3585, \"to\": 3631, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The artistic gymnastic competition at the Paris Olympics 2024 will be contested from 27 July to 5 August at theBercy Arena.\", \"from\": 3633, \"to\": 3756, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"South Africa hasneverwon a gymnastics medal in its Olympic history.\", \"from\": 3758, \"to\": 3825, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3758, \"end\": 3770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2478226451190822e-17, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As reported byThe South African website, theSouth African Sports Confederation, Olympic and Paralympic Committee (Sascoc)has confirmed the prize money on offer for any South African medal winners - as well as their coaches.\", \"from\": 3827, \"to\": 4050, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"- Athletes who win gold will be awardedR400 000, with the coach receivingR100 000  - Silver medalists will earnR200 000andR50 000for the coach  - Bronze medal payouts will beR75 000andR25 000for the athlete and coach, respectively  Women:Caitlin Rooskrantz (artistic)  Coach/Manager:Ilse Pelser (coach)  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring!\", \"from\": 4052, \"to\": 4435, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4356, \"end\": 4359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WIN_Television\", \"score\": 0.9906043577547436